5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDonations%20started%20pouring%20in%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Strangers%20left%20messages%20of%20encouragement%2C%20prayers%2C%20and%20hope.%20Within%20a%20week%2C%20over%20%2410%2C000%20had%20been%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20humbling.%20I%20remember%20sitting%20with%20tears%20in%20my%20eyes%2C%20grateful%20that%20someone%20%E2%80%94%20many%20people%20%E2%80%94%20cared.%20I%20emailed%20some%20of%20the%20donors%20to%20thank%20them.%20One%20woman%20responded%20kindly%2C%20and%20I%20sent%20her%20a%20photo%20of%20Levi%20in%20return.%20She%20replied%20with%20a%20message%20that%20would%20become%20a%20lifeline%20for%20me%20in%20the%20months%20to%20come%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLevi%20will%20be%20home%2C%20and%20he%20will%20heal%20well%2C%20and%20you%20will%20be%20loving%20him%20up%20soon.%20Of%20that%20I%20am%20sure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ef8849f-75f2-42ac-8ecf-48b39386c44e%5C%22%3EI%20didn't%20know%20how%20much%20I%20needed%20those%20words%20until%20they%20became%20my%20anchor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20stood%20out%20wasn't%20just%20the%20sentiment%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20certainty.%20That%20confidence%20from%20a%20stranger%2C%20spoken%20without%20hesitation%2C%20felt%20like%20a%20warm%20blanket%20wrapped%20around%20a%20shivering%20soul.%20It%20reminded%20me%20that%20sometimes%2C%20even%20when%20things%20are%20falling%20apart%2C%20someone%20else's%20belief%20can%20keep%20you%20stitched%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20things%20did%20fall%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevi%20didn't%20wake%20up%20a%20few%20days%20after%20surgery%20like%20many%20babies%20do.%20He%20was%20hooked%20up%20to%20tubes%20and%20surrounded%20by%20machines%20for%20weeks.%20The%20left%20side%20of%20his%20heart%2C%20which%20had%20been%20compromised%20from%20the%20start%2C%20remained%20weak.%20Then%20the%20right%20side%20began%20failing.%20He%20developed%20two%20blood%20infections%2C%20then%20thrombosis%20in%20his%20groin%20and%20neck.%20Fluid%20built%20up%20around%20his%20heart%20and%20lungs.%20The%20complications%20were%20relentless.%20Every%20step%20forward%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20setback.%20I%20began%20to%20fear%20that%20maybe%20we%20wouldn't%20get%20the%20storybook%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20that%20stranger's%20words%20echoed%20in%20my%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20repeated%20them%20to%20myself%20like%20a%20mantra%20on%20long%20rides%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20on%20tear-streaked%20days%20when%20doctors%20couldn't%20give%20answers%2C%20on%20quiet%20nights%20when%20I'd%20sit%20with%20my%20girls%20and%20pretend%20everything%20was%20normal.%20Her%20assurance%20carried%20me%20when%20I%20had%20nothing%20left%20to%20hold%20onto.%20That%20confidence%20became%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e9772a96-4a88-4c49-b574-5d689f19c31b%5C%22%3EHe%20came%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20held%20him%20%E2%80%94%20really%20held%20him%20%E2%80%94%20was%2055%20days%20after%20he%20was%20born.%20I%20had%20dreamt%20of%20that%20moment%2C%20but%20nothing%20could've%20prepared%20me%20for%20the%20wave%20of%20emotion%20that%20hit.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20let%20go.%20I%20finally%20had%20my%20son%20in%20my%20arms.%20He%20smelled%20like%20hospital%20soap%20and%20baby%20lotion%20and%20something%20uniquely%20his.%20I%20cried%2C%20and%20I%20smiled%2C%20and%20I%20told%20him%20I%20was%20proud%20of%20how%20strong%20he%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20weeks%20passed%20and%20Levi%20slowly%20began%20to%20heal%2C%20I%20stayed%20close.%20I%20held%20him%20through%20setbacks%20and%20celebrated%20every%20little%20win%3A%20a%20removed%20tube%2C%20a%20better%20scan%2C%20a%20good%20day%20with%20no%20new%20alarms.%20And%20then%2C%20one%20day%2C%20it%20was%20over.%20No%20more%20timed%20visits.%20No%20more%20sterile%20gowns%20and%20masks.%20Just%20me%2C%20my%20baby%20boy%2C%20and%20the%20chance%20to%20love%20him%20freely%2C%20just%20like%20she%20said%20I%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20finally%20discharged%2C%20I%20wrote%20that%20stranger%20again%3A%20%26quot%3BHe%20made%20it.%20He's%20coming%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20responded%20with%20joy%2C%20and%20we%20still%20exchange%20messages%20now%20and%20then.%20I%20send%20her%20updates%2C%20photos%2C%20and%20a%20small%20window%20into%20the%20life%20she%20had%20faith%20he%20would%20eventually%20have.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20world%20that%20can%20often%20feel%20indifferent%20or%20rushed%2C%20her%20words%20were%20a%20stillness.%20They%20were%20a%20pause%2C%20a%20gift%2C%20even.%20She%20didn't%20have%20to%20say%20anything%20at%20all%2C%20but%20she%20did.%20And%20what%20she%20said%20mattered%20more%20than%20she'll%20ever%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstranger-gave-me-hope-baby-nicu-recovery-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753906201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6840518a9d73a0031e8dd70f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstranger-gave-me-hope-baby-nicu-recovery-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20son%20needed%20open%20heart%20surgery%20at%205%20days%20old%20and%20I%20couldn't%20hold%20him%20for%2055%20days.%20A%20stranger's%20words%20gave%20me%20the%20hope%20I%20needed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(%20Creshonda%20Smith)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstranger-gave-me-hope-baby-nicu-recovery-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Authoritarian%20states%20operating%20without%20impunity%20to%20silence%20dissidents%20in%20UK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753904520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F12%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-chloe-cheung-hong-kong_6784559.jpg%3F20241224120147%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%