0of%20firewood%2C%20or%20fishing%20inside%20the%20forests%E2%80%A6the%20peasants%20collected%20fish%2C%20mostly%20as%20their%20daily%20food%20requirements%20and%20also%20for%20their%20petty%20trade%20with%20the%20help%20of%20locally%20developed%20traps%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20through%20dialogue%2C%20Mahi%20sparked%20change%20in%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Mising%20activist%20Doley%20shared%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3ERoundglass%20Sustain%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CMiri%20had%20the%20advantage%20of%20being%20a%20Mising%20tribesman%20and%20thus%20was%20in%20a%20position%20to%20empathise%20with%20the%20tribes%20in%20Kaziranga.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20A%20J%20Milroy%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20conservator%20of%20the%20Assam%20Forest%20Department%2C%20he%20blazed%20a%20trail%20to%20amp%20up%20efforts%20to%20stop%20poaching.%20Their%20efforts%20culminated%20in%20Kaziranga%20being%20opened%20to%20visitors%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%201938.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20also%20supervised%20the%20capture%20of%20the%20first%20live%20rhino%20in%20Kaziranga%2C%20which%20was%20later%20sent%20to%20a%20zoo%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20As%20Tridip%20shares%2C%20when%20waters%20inundated%20the%20Karbi-Anglong%20area%20in%20Assam%20in%201939%2C%20Mahi%20chose%20to%20stay%20back%20and%20assist%20the%20locals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20also%20how%20he%20contracted%20Black%20Fever%2C%20which%20later%20took%20his%20life%20at%20the%20young%20age%20of%2036%20in%201939%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Tridip.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20passed%20away%20at%20an%20early%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20legacy%20lives%20on%20in%20the%20landscape%20of%20Kaziranga%2C%20a%20dream%20he%20channelled%20all%20his%20efforts%20into.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20